data.mission: Create a small fixed DOI test set, run api_server.py end-to-end to resolve sources/metadata, and save results to runtime/_build/tables/doi_results.csv and runtime/_build/reports/doi_run_report.json with explicit success/failure reasons per DOI.

Design a stable ID spec (e.g., `item_id`, `claim_id`, `source_id`) and implement a mismatch checker that fails CI on inconsistency; include a demo fixture that intentionally triggers mismatches and captures diagnostic output.

After consolidation, run the DOI retrieval workflow (doi_retriever.py and/or api_server.py) on a small fixed DOI list and write an inspectable results CSV (per-DOI status + reason) into runtime/_build/tables/doi_results.csv, plus a JSON report into runtime/_build/reports/doi_run.json.

Run and validate the cross-artifact ID checker deliverables (e.g., `id_schema.py`, `id_mismatch_demo.py`, any CSVâ†”JSONL join checks) against a small passing fixture and a small failing fixture, then emit a human-readable report (`runtime/_build/reports/id_validation.md`) and a machine-readable report (`runtime/_build/reports/id_validation.json`).

Execute the DOI retrieval workflow script(s) already created (e.g., `doi_retriever.py`) on a fixed DOI fixture list and write per-DOI output JSON files under `runtime/_build/doi/` plus a summary table `runtime/_build/tables/doi_retrieval_summary.csv` that includes status and failure reasons.
